 Completed Task 4: Sentiment Analysis using NLP 📊🧠

I'm excited to share my latest Data Analytics project focused on Sentiment Analysis, where I explored how Natural Language Processing (NLP) can transform unstructured text into meaningful business insights.

🔍 Project Highlights

✅ Collected and analyzed text data from Amazon reviews, social media posts, and news headlines.
✅ Classified customer opinions into Positive, Negative, and Neutral sentiments using NLP techniques.
✅ Applied text preprocessing, tokenization, stop-word removal, and sentiment scoring with TextBlob.
✅ Performed Emotion Detection to identify emotions such as Joy, Anger, Sadness, Fear, Trust, and Surprise.
✅ Built insightful visualizations including sentiment distribution, word clouds, rating analysis, emotion analysis, and trend charts.
✅ Generated actionable business insights to support marketing strategies, product development, and customer experience improvements.

🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- NLTK
- TextBlob
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- WordCloud
- Jupyter Notebook

📈 Key Business Insights

📌 Most customer reviews expressed positive sentiment.
📌 Product quality received strong appreciation from users.
📌 Pricing and delivery were the most common reasons for negative feedback.
📌 Sentiment trends can help organizations improve products, strengthen customer satisfaction, and make data-driven decisions.

This project strengthened my practical skills in Natural Language Processing (NLP), Sentiment Analysis, Data Visualization, Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), and Business Intelligence.

